可得

$$
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{M} &amp;= 
\begin{bmatrix}
 m &amp; 0 \\
 0 &amp; m
\end{bmatrix}, \quad
\mathbf{A} =
\begin{bmatrix}
 \cos\theta_1 &amp; \sin\theta_1 &amp; 0 \\
 \cos\theta_1 &amp; \sin\theta_1 &amp; \cos\theta_2 &amp; \sin\theta_2
\end{bmatrix}, \\
\mathbf{e} &amp;= 
\begin{pmatrix}
 1 \\
 -mg\theta_2
\end{pmatrix}, \quad
\mathbf{Mv} =
\begin{bmatrix}
 \dot{\theta}_1^2(-\sin\theta_1 + \cos\theta_1) \\
 -(\sin\theta_1\dot{\theta}_1^2 + \sin\theta_2\dot{\theta}_2^2) + (\cos\theta_1\dot{\theta}_1^2 + \cos\theta_2\dot{\theta}_2^2)
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}
$$

代入方程可得

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
2 &amp; \cos(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\cos(\theta_1 - \theta_2) &amp; 1 \\
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
\ddot{\theta}_1 \\
\ddot{\theta}_2 \\
\end{bmatrix}
+
\begin{bmatrix}
\dot{\theta}_2^2 \sin(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\dot{\theta}_1^2 \sin(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\end{bmatrix}
=\begin{bmatrix}
-\frac{g}{l} \sin\theta_1 \\
-\frac{g}{l} \sin\theta_2 \\
\end{bmatrix}
$$"><p>由<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="10.638ex" height="2.163ex" role="img" focusable="false" viewBox="0 -762 4702 956" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" div.data-content:
由$\ddot r = A \ddot q + v$

可得

$$
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{M} &=
\begin{bmatrix}
m & 0 \\
0 & m
\end{bmatrix}, \quad
\mathbf{A} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos\theta_1 & \sin\theta_1 & 0 \\
\cos\theta_1 & \sin\theta_1 & \cos\theta_2 & \sin\theta_2
\end{bmatrix}, \\
\mathbf{e} &=
\begin{pmatrix}
1 \\
-mg\theta_2
\end{pmatrix}, \quad
\mathbf{Mv} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\dot{\theta}_1^2(-\sin\theta_1 + \cos\theta_1) \\
-(\sin\theta_1\dot{\theta}_1^2 + \sin\theta_2\dot{\theta}_2^2) + (\cos\theta_1\dot{\theta}_1^2 + \cos\theta_2\dot{\theta}_2^2)
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}
$$

代入方程可得

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
2 & \cos(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\cos(\theta_1 - \theta_2) & 1 \\
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
\ddot{\theta}_1 \\
\ddot{\theta}_2 \\
\end{bmatrix}
+
\begin{bmatrix}
\dot{\theta}_2^2 \sin(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\dot{\theta}_1^2 \sin(\theta_1 - \theta_2) \\
\end{bmatrix}
=\begin{bmatrix}
-\frac{g}{l} \sin\theta_1 \\
-\frac{g}{l} \sin\theta_2 \\
\end{bmatrix}
$$
